hpicfOspfv3MIB.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfOspfv3MIB.description: The MIB module contains HP proprietary extensions to the OSPFV3-MIB module.

hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetric.name: hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetric
hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetric.description: The default metric used for advertising external routes by this router.

hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetricType.name: hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetricType
hpicfOspfv3DefaultImportMetricType.description: The default metric type used for advertising external routes by this router.

hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance.name: hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance
hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance.description: The administrative distance to associate with intra-area routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes over inter-area or AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance or hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance is lower than hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance.name: hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance
hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance.description: The administrative distance to associate with inter-area routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes over inter-area routes, even if hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance is lower than hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance. It will also still prefer inter-area routes over AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance is lower than hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance.name: hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance
hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance.description: The administrative distance to associate with AS-external routes learned by OSPF. Routes with lower distances are preferred. By default, OSPF routes have an administrative distance of 110. Note that the administrative distance settings for OSPF do not affect the choice of routes within OSPF. OSPF will still prefer intra-area routes and inter-area routes over AS-external routes even if hpicfOspfv3ExternalDistance is lower than the hpicfOspfv3IntraAreaDistance or hpicfOspfv3InterAreaDistance. The appropriate administrative distance value is applied to the route that OSPF selects as its best route to a destination and is used to decide whether OSPF's route is preferred over a route from some other source.

hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleWaitInterval.name: hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleWaitInterval
hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleWaitInterval.description: Minimum wait time between two consecutive SPFs When spf throttle is triggered.

hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleMaxWaitTime.name: hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleMaxWaitTime
hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleMaxWaitTime.description: Maximum time between two consecutive SPFs runs when spf throttling active.

hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval.name: hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval
hpicfOspfv3SpfThrottleCurrentSpfInterval.description: Current dynamic wait interval between SPF computations

hpicfOspfv3AreaCount.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaCount
hpicfOspfv3AreaCount.description: Number of areas in a router

hpicfOspfv3RestartHelper.name: hpicfOspfv3RestartHelper
hpicfOspfv3RestartHelper.description: Graceful restart helper status A value of true (1) indicates that Restart helper is enabled, false(2) indicates that Restart helper is disabled.

hpicfOspfv3ASscopeUnknownLsaCount.name: hpicfOspfv3ASscopeUnknownLsaCount
hpicfOspfv3ASscopeUnknownLsaCount.description: The total number of AS-scope unknown link state advertisements received.

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbStatLinkLsa.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbStatLinkLsa
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbStatLinkLsa.description: This object indicates total number of Link LSAs in the router.

hpicfOspfv3TotalUnknownLsa.name: hpicfOspfv3TotalUnknownLsa
hpicfOspfv3TotalUnknownLsa.description: This object indicates total number of LSAs received with Unknown type.

hpicfOspfv3ReferenceCost.name: hpicfOspfv3ReferenceCost
hpicfOspfv3ReferenceCost.description: The reference cost is used as global configuration for internal area cost & vlan cost.

hpicfOspfv3IfMetricTable.name: hpicfOspfv3IfMetricTable
hpicfOspfv3IfMetricTable.description: Extensions to the table that contains OSPF Metric specific information.

hpicfOspfv3IfMetricEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3IfMetricEntry
hpicfOspfv3IfMetricEntry.description: A list of extensions to the information maintained for an OSPF interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfFlagValue.name: hpicfOspfv3IfFlagValue
hpicfOspfv3IfFlagValue.description: This flag is defined to know the type of OSPF cost configuration.. -1 : Default configuration. 0 : Manual configuration. 1 : Global configuration (value taken from global).

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbTable
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 AS-Scope Link State Database (LSDB). The LSDB contains the AS-Scope Link State Advertisements from throughout the areas that the device is attached to.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEntry
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEFTFlags.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEFTFlags
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbEFTFlags.description: A 32-bit integer Representing the E,F and T bit flags

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbMetric.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbMetric
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbMetric.description: The cost associated with this route.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixLength.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixLength
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixLength.description: The Prefix Length of the Address Prefix.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixOptions.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixOptions
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbPrefixOptions.description: The Prefix Options associated with the Address Prefix.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsType.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsType
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsType.description: If non-zero value, this refers to another LSA type in Link State Database further identified by the Reference Link State ID field

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbFwdingAddress.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbFwdingAddress
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbFwdingAddress.description: If included, Data traffic for the advertised destination will be forwarded to this address.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbExtRouteTags.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbExtRouteTags
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbExtRouteTags.description: The 32-bit Route Tag for the advertised Route.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsId.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsId
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbRefLsId.description: The 32-bit Link state ID of the referenced LSA entry.

hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbLsaLength.name: hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbLsaLength
hpicfOspfv3AsLsdbLsaLength.description: This field describes the length of LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbTable
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Area-Scope link state database. The LSDB contains the Area-Scope Link State Advertisements from throughout the area that the device is attached to.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRtrCapBits.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRtrCapBits
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRtrCapBits.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.4.2 Router LSAs, RFC5340
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRtrCapBits.description: This field is valid only for Router LSA. It represents the capabilities of the router in the Area.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbOptions.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbOptions
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 The Options field
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbOptions.description: The Options field enables OSPF routers to support (or not support) optional capabilities, and to communicate their capability level to other OSPF routers. This field is valid if the LSA is a Router LSA or a Network LSA, or an Inter-Area-Router LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbMetric.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbMetric
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbMetric.description: This field is valid only for Router LSA, a Inter-Area_prefix LSA or a NSSA LSA. This field indicates the cost involved in using the interface or route.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixLength.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixLength
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixLength.description: The Prefix Length of the Address Prefix.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixOptions.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixOptions
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbPrefixOptions.description: The Prefix Options associated with the Address Prefix.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbDstRtrId.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbDstRtrId
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbDstRtrId.description: The Router ID of the router being described by the LSA. This field is valid if the LSA is a Inter-Area-Router LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbNumPrefixes.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbNumPrefixes
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbNumPrefixes.description: This field is valid only for Inter-Area-Prefix LSA and indicates the number of prefixes in the LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsType.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsType
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsType.description: This field is valid only for Inter-Area-Prefix LSA or a NSSA LSA. If non-zero, an LSA with this LS type is to be associated with this LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsId.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsId
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefLsId.description: This field is valid only for Inter-Area-Prefix LSA or a NSSA LSA. This field is included only if the Reference LS Type field is set and identifies the LSA with this Link State ID.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefAdvRtrId.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefAdvRtrId
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbRefAdvRtrId.description: This field is valid only for Inter-Area-Prefix LSA or a NSSA LSA. This field is included only if the Reference LS Type field is set and identifies the LSA having this Router ID as the advertising Router ID.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEFTFlags.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEFTFlags
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbEFTFlags.description: This field is valid only for NSSA LSA. This field represents the E,F and T bit flags

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbFwdingAddress.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbFwdingAddress
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbFwdingAddress.description: This field is valid only for NSSA LSA. This field is present only if the 'F' Bit is set in the EFT flags field and if included, the data traffic for the advertised destination will be forwarded to this address.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbExtRouteTags.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbExtRouteTags
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbExtRouteTags.description: This field is valid only for NSSA LSA. This field is present only if the 'T' Bit is set in the EFT flags field. A 32-bit field which may be used to communicate additional information between AS boundary routers.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLsaLength.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLsaLength
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLsaLength.description: This field describes the length of LSA.

hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLinks.name: hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLinks
hpicfOspfv3AreaLsdbLinks.description: This field describes the number of links.

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbTable
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Link-Scope link state database(LSDB) for non-virtual interfaces. The LSDB contains the Link-Scope Link State Advertisements from the interfaces that the device is attached to.

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-Scope Link State Advertisement.

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbRtrPriority.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbRtrPriority
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbRtrPriority.description: This field is the OSPF priority set for this router

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbOptions.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbOptions
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 The Options field
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbOptions.description: The Options field enables OSPF routers to support (or not support) optional capabilities, and to communicate their capability level to other OSPF routers.

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLocalAddress.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLocalAddress
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLocalAddress.description: The advertising router's link local IPv6 address

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbNumPrefixes.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbNumPrefixes
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbNumPrefixes.description: The number of other links on the advertising router

hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLsaLength.name: hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLsaLength
hpicfOspfv3LinkLsdbLsaLength.description: This field describes the length of LSA.

hpicfOspfv3IfTable.name: hpicfOspfv3IfTable
hpicfOspfv3IfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
hpicfOspfv3IfTable.description: The table describes the Ospfv3 interfaces.

hpicfOspfv3IfEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3IfEntry
hpicfOspfv3IfEntry.description: The Entry describes one Ospfv3 interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfPassive.name: hpicfOspfv3IfPassive
hpicfOspfv3IfPassive.description: The passive state configuration of the OSPF interface. In the passive mode no OSPF protocol messages are exchanged on this interface. true (1) - The interface is configured to work in Passive mode false (2) - The interface is configured to work in normal mode. This is the default configuration. Changing the value will cause OSPF to reset on this interface and make necessary adjustments to the link state database. All other operations are not defined and will not affect the state of the protocol.

hpicfOspfv3IfNbrCount.name: hpicfOspfv3IfNbrCount
hpicfOspfv3IfNbrCount.description: This object specifies the number of OSPFv3 neighbors reachable via this interface. This counter should be incremented when a new neighbor is added in the network in which this interface is present. It should be decremented when a neighbor is disconnected.

hpicfOspfv3IfDRAddr.name: hpicfOspfv3IfDRAddr
hpicfOspfv3IfDRAddr.description: This object specifies link local ipv6 address of Designated Router on the interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfBDRAddr.name: hpicfOspfv3IfBDRAddr
hpicfOspfv3IfBDRAddr.description: This object specifies link local ipv6 address of Backup Designated Router on the interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfHelloDueTime.name: hpicfOspfv3IfHelloDueTime
hpicfOspfv3IfHelloDueTime.description: This object specifies the time remaining for the hello timer for the particular Interface to expire.

hpicfOspfv3IfAdjNbrCount.name: hpicfOspfv3IfAdjNbrCount
hpicfOspfv3IfAdjNbrCount.description: This object specifies the number of fully adjacent neighbors present on this interface. This counter should be incremented when a new neighbor becomes fully adjacent. It should be decremented when the neighbor goes out from full state.

hpicfOspfv3NbrTable.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrTable
hpicfOspfv3NbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
hpicfOspfv3NbrTable.description: A table describing all neighbors of the of the OSPFv3 router.

hpicfOspfv3NbrEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrEntry
hpicfOspfv3NbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
hpicfOspfv3NbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

hpicfOspfv3NbrUpTime.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrUpTime
hpicfOspfv3NbrUpTime.description: This object specifies the time duration in seconds for which the adjacency with a particular neighbor is active. This should be a monotonically increasing timer for the duration till the adjacency is active. This counter should be reset on losing and re-establishing an adjacency

hpicfOspfv3NbrTimeToExpiry.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrTimeToExpiry
hpicfOspfv3NbrTimeToExpiry.description: This object specifies the time remaining for the dead timer for the particular neighbor to expire. This counter thus specifies the time in seconds left for an adjacency to be brought down in case no hello packet is received during that interval.

hpicfOspfv3NbrDataBaseSummary.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrDataBaseSummary
hpicfOspfv3NbrDataBaseSummary.description: The number of Link State Advertisements (LSA) sent in Database Description (DD)packet.

hpicfOspfv3NbrLinkStateRequest.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrLinkStateRequest
hpicfOspfv3NbrLinkStateRequest.description: The number of Link State Advertisements (LSA) in link state request list.

hpicfOspfv3NbrRestartState.name: hpicfOspfv3NbrRestartState
hpicfOspfv3NbrRestartState.description: Describes the Graceful Restart(GR) state. normal(0) - Indicates normal status helper(1) - Helper indicates the router is helping another router which is currently in graceful restart.

hpicfOspfv3IfStatsTable.name: hpicfOspfv3IfStatsTable
hpicfOspfv3IfStatsTable.description: Table that contains OSPFv3 Interface traffic specific statistics.

hpicfOspfv3IfStatsEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3IfStatsEntry
hpicfOspfv3IfStatsEntry.description: A list of statistics counters maintained for an OSPFv3 interface traffic information.

hpicfOspfv3IfSentHelloPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentHelloPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfSentHelloPkt.description: The number of OSPFv3 Hello packets sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time an OSPFv3 Hello packet is sent out of an OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfSentDDPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentDDPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfSentDDPkt.description: The number of Database Description packets sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time an OSPFv3 DD packet is sent out of an OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSRPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSRPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSRPkt.description: The number of Link State Request packets sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time OSPFv3 LSR packet is sent out of an OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSUPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSUPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSUPkt.description: The number of Link State Update packets sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time OSPFv3 LSU packet is sent out of an OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command.

hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSAPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSAPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfSentLSAPkt.description: The number of Link State Acknowledgement packet sent on the interface. This number is incremented each time OSPFv3 LS Ack packet is sent out of an OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command.

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdHelloPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdHelloPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdHelloPkt.description: The number of Hello packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a hello packet is received on OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdDDPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdDDPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdDDPkt.description: The number of Database Description packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPFv3 DD packet is received on OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSRPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSRPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSRPkt.description: The number of Link State Request packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPFv3 LSR packet is received on OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSUPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSUPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSUPkt.description: The number of Link State Update packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time an OSPFv3 LSU packet is received on OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSAPkt.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSAPkt
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdLSAPkt.description: The number of Link State Acknowledgement packets received on the interface. This number is incremented each time a OSPF LS Ack packet is received on OSPFv3 enabled interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command

hpicfOspfv3IfSentTotalErrorCount.name: hpicfOspfv3IfSentTotalErrorCount
hpicfOspfv3IfSentTotalErrorCount.description: This refers to the number of erroneous packets discarded on an OSPFv3 interface while sending errors. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdTotalErrorCount.name: hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdTotalErrorCount
hpicfOspfv3IfRcvdTotalErrorCount.description: This refers to the number of erroneous packets received on an OSPFv3 interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

hpicfOspfv3IfErrorTable.name: hpicfOspfv3IfErrorTable
hpicfOspfv3IfErrorTable.description: Table that contains OSPFv3 Interface traffic specific error information.

hpicfOspfv3IfErrorEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3IfErrorEntry
hpicfOspfv3IfErrorEntry.description: A list of error counters maintained for an OSPFv3 interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfErrorType.name: hpicfOspfv3IfErrorType
hpicfOspfv3IfErrorType.description: This refers to the type of errors in the OSPFv3 packet received on an OSPFv3 enabled interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfErrorCount.name: hpicfOspfv3IfErrorCount
hpicfOspfv3IfErrorCount.description: This refers to the number of erroneous packets received on an OSPFv3 interface for each error type. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system. The counters can be cleared for any interface using 'clear ipv6 ospf3 statistics' command.

hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsTable.name: hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsTable
hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsTable.description: A list used to clear statistics information maintained for an OSPFv3 interface.

hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsEntry.name: hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsEntry
hpicfOspfv3IfClearStatsEntry.description: A list used to clear statistics information maintained for an OSPFv3 interface.

hpicfOspfv3SetTrap.name: hpicfOspfv3SetTrap
hpicfOspfv3SetTrap.description: A four-octet string serving as a bit map for the trap events defined by the OSPFv3 traps. This object is used to enable or disable specific OSPFv3 traps where a 1 in the bit field represents enabled. The right-most bit (least significant) represents trap 0. Trap Name BitMap ---------------------------------------- OSPFV3_IF_STATE_CHANGE 0x00001 OSPFV3_VIRT_IF_STATE_CHANGE 0x00002 OSPFV3_NBR_STATE_CHANGE 0x00004 OSPFV3_VIRT_NBR_STATE_CHANGE 0x00008 OSPFV3_INTF_CONFIG_ERROR 0x00010 OSPFV3_VIRT_INTF_CONFIG_ERROR 0x00020 OSPFV3_INTF_RCV_BAD_PKT 0x00040 OSPFV3_VIRT_INTF_RCV_BAD_PKT 0x00080 OSPFV3_RST_STATUS 0x20000 OSPFV3_NBR_RST_HELP_STATUS 0x40000 OSPFV3_VIRT_NBR_RST_HELP_STAT 0x80000 OSPFV3_ALL_TRAPS 0xE00FF
